hpSwitchBasicConfigMIB.name: hpSwitchBasicConfigMIB
hpSwitchBasicConfigMIB.contactinfo: Hewlett Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpSwitchBasicConfigMIB.description: This MIB module describes objects for basic switch configuration.

hpSwitchSaveConfig.name: hpSwitchSaveConfig
hpSwitchSaveConfig.description: When this object is set to to 'saveConfig' it results in saving the running configuration of the switch to flash. The saved configuration becomes the boot-up configuration of the switch when it boots next time. When read, this object always returns 'noConfigSave'.

hpSwitchAliasTable.name: hpSwitchAliasTable
hpSwitchAliasTable.description: Table of alias configurations for CLI commands. This table contains information about name of the alias and the corresponding CLI command.

hpSwitchAliasEntry.name: hpSwitchAliasEntry
hpSwitchAliasEntry.description: A row in the alias config table.

hpSwitchAliasName.name: hpSwitchAliasName
hpSwitchAliasName.description: Name of the alias which uniquely identifies alias configuration table. 'hpSwitchAliasName' can be used in place of 'hpSwitchAliasCommand` on the CLI. Maximum allowed length for alias name is 32 characters.

hpSwitchAliasCommand.name: hpSwitchAliasCommand
hpSwitchAliasCommand.description: CLI command for which 'hpSwitchAliasName' can be used in CLI. Maximum allowed length for alias command is 255 characters. This object is required to create an entry in the table.

hpSwitchAliasConfigRowStatus.name: hpSwitchAliasConfigRowStatus
hpSwitchAliasConfigRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in alias table. Row cant be created when 'hpSwitchAliasCommand' is of zero length. Row transition to 'notReady' or 'notInService' states are not allowed.

hpicfBridgeFilterConfigTable.name: hpicfBridgeFilterConfigTable
hpicfBridgeFilterConfigTable.description: A table that contains information about the source port traffic filter configuration in this device.

hpicfBridgeFilterConfigEntry.name: hpicfBridgeFilterConfigEntry
hpicfBridgeFilterConfigEntry.description: Information about a source port traffic filter configuration in this device.

hpicfBridgeFilterName.name: hpicfBridgeFilterName
hpicfBridgeFilterName.description: This variable specifies the name of the filter. Filter name can be upto 20 characters. Filter name cannot contain tilde (~). A filter name can not be same as port-name.

hpicfBridgeFilterDropPortMask.name: hpicfBridgeFilterDropPortMask
hpicfBridgeFilterDropPortMask.description: This variable specifies a group of ports to which forwarding of filtered traffic is not permitted.

hpicfBridgeFilterEntryStatus.name: hpicfBridgeFilterEntryStatus
hpicfBridgeFilterEntryStatus.description: Row can be deleted only when no port are mapped to this filter in 'hpSwitchFilterConfigEntry' table.

hpSwitchAclLogtimeoutConfig.name: hpSwitchAclLogtimeoutConfig
hpSwitchAclLogtimeoutConfig.description: The time in seconds between ACL logging summary messages. Some devices may limit the range to 30..300.

hpSwitchAclIpv4DenyFragmentedTcpHeader.name: hpSwitchAclIpv4DenyFragmentedTcpHeader
hpSwitchAclIpv4DenyFragmentedTcpHeader.description: Configure the device to drop all IPv4 packets containing a fragmented TCP header.

hpSwitchAclIpv6DenyNonClassifiableL4Head.name: hpSwitchAclIpv6DenyNonClassifiableL4Header
hpSwitchAclIpv6DenyNonClassifiableL4Head.description: Configure the device to drop all IPv6 packets for which the Layer 4 header cannot be processed by ACL hardware.

hpSwitchAclGroupingEnable.name: hpSwitchAclGroupingEnable
hpSwitchAclGroupingEnable.description: This object enables or disables ACL Grouping support. When set to true(1), ACL Grouping will allow for the sharing of hardware entries from an ACL with the same name and type and applied in the same direction when the hpicfGppcv2AcSharedFlag is used to apply the ACL. When set to false(2), entries will be unshared.

hpSwitchIgmpProxyDomainConfigTable.name: hpSwitchIgmpProxyDomainConfigTable
hpSwitchIgmpProxyDomainConfigTable.description: A table that contains information about the IGMP proxy domain configurations on this switch.

hpSwitchIgmpProxyDomainConfigEntry.name: hpSwitchIgmpProxyDomainConfigEntry
hpSwitchIgmpProxyDomainConfigEntry.description: The information associated with each IGMP proxy domain configuration.

hpSwitchIgmpProxyDomainId.name: hpSwitchIgmpProxyDomainId
hpSwitchIgmpProxyDomainId.description: The domain id that uniquely identifies a row in the IGMP proxy domain configuration table.

hpSwitchIgmpProxyDomainStatus.name: hpSwitchIgmpProxyDomainStatus
hpSwitchIgmpProxyDomainStatus.description: The status of a IGMP proxy domain configuration entry. Allows creation/deletion of the IGMP proxy domain entry. Row cannot be deleted if the IGMP proxy domain is associated with a VLAN.

hpSwitchIgmpProxyMcastLowerIp.name: hpSwitchIgmpProxyMcastLowerIp
hpSwitchIgmpProxyMcastLowerIp.description: The IGMP proxy domain's lower multicast IP.

hpSwitchIgmpProxyMcastUpperIp.name: hpSwitchIgmpProxyMcastUpperIp
hpSwitchIgmpProxyMcastUpperIp.description: The IGMP proxy domain's upper multicast IP.

hpicfPortCopyNameTable.name: hpicfPortCopyNameTable
hpicfPortCopyNameTable.description: This table contains Mirroring Destination name String.

hpicfPortCopyNameEntry.name: hpicfPortCopyNameEntry
hpicfPortCopyNameEntry.description: An entry in the hpicfPortCopyNameEntry contains Mirroring Destination name string.

hpSwitchDefaultLogon.name: hpSwitchDefaultLogon
hpSwitchDefaultLogon.description: This indicates whether switch should boot to CLI (default) or menu. The changes takes effect after rebooting the switch.

hpSwitchChassisLocateTable.name: hpSwitchChassisLocateTable
hpSwitchChassisLocateTable.description: This table is contains information about the current state of all the chassis locate LEDs.

hpSwitchChassisLocateEntry.name: hpSwitchChassisLocateEntry
hpSwitchChassisLocateEntry.description: Contains information about the current state of a particular chassis LED.

hpSwitchChassisLocateState.name: hpSwitchChassisLocateState
hpSwitchChassisLocateState.description: The current state of the chassis locate LED.

hpSwitchChassisLocateDuration.name: hpSwitchChassisLocateDuration
hpSwitchChassisLocateDuration.description: The duration for which the current LED state is to be maintained. The minimum value is 60 and the maximum value is 86400. The 'off' state does not require a duration. A get request for the duration when the state is 'off' will return the default duration value.

hpSwitchChassisLocateWhen.name: hpSwitchChassisLocateWhen
hpSwitchChassisLocateWhen.description: When to apply the values specified by hpSwitchChassisLocateState and hpSwitchChassisLocateDuration. If not specified, the default is now.

hpSwitchModuleInfoTable.name: hpSwitchModuleInfoTable
hpSwitchModuleInfoTable.description: A table describing all modules that can be supported by the device.

hpSwitchModuleInfoEntry.name: hpSwitchModuleInfoEntry
hpSwitchModuleInfoEntry.description: The information regarding the module type in the switch. This table lists all the supported module types. The supported module type will have the equivalent module name.

hpSwitchModuleInfoModId.name: hpSwitchModuleInfoModId
hpSwitchModuleInfoModId.description: The module Id. This is a sequence number

hpSwitchModuleInfoModType.name: hpSwitchModuleInfoModType
hpSwitchModuleInfoModType.description: The module type in the switch. This is the Jnumber string that is supported on the device.

hpSwitchModuleConfigTable.name: hpSwitchModuleConfigTable
hpSwitchModuleConfigTable.description: A table to configure the module type for a specific module.

hpSwitchModuleConfigEntry.name: hpSwitchModuleConfigEntry
hpSwitchModuleConfigEntry.description: This entry is used to configure the module type for a specific module. Configuration of module type is not allowed if it is already configured.

hpSwitchModuleConfigModType.name: hpSwitchModuleConfigModType
hpSwitchModuleConfigModType.description: The module type in the switch. This is the Jnumber supported on the device. The supported types are listed in hpSwitchModuleInfoTable.

hpSwitchModuleConfigModName.name: hpSwitchModuleConfigModName
hpSwitchModuleConfigModName.description: The module name in the switch.

hpSwitchModuleConfigModRemove.name: hpSwitchModuleConfigModRemove
hpSwitchModuleConfigModRemove.description: This MIB object is used to remove the slot configuration. Setting this object to true (1) will remove the module configuration. Default value is false (2). This object should always returns false (2). The module can be configured by setting the hpSwitchModuleConfigModType to a supported Jnumber on the device.

hpSwitchWebSupportUrl.name: hpSwitchWebSupportUrl
hpSwitchWebSupportUrl.description: URL for the web interface support page.

hpSwitchStartupConfigSeqNum.name: hpSwitchStartupConfigSeqNum
hpSwitchStartupConfigSeqNum.description: This is the value of the global startup-config sequential number. Every change to startup-config increments the value by 1. Must be stored in non-volatile memory to be carried over the system boot.

hpSwitchStartupConfigNotifyEnable.name: hpSwitchStartupConfigNotifyEnable
hpSwitchStartupConfigNotifyEnable.description: Indicates whether the SNMP entity is permitted to generate hpSwitchStartupConfigChange notifications. Default is disabled.

hpSwitchImplicitConfigSave.name: hpSwitchImplicitConfigSave
hpSwitchImplicitConfigSave.description: This object is to enable/disable the implicit write-memory (saving the running-config to the flash) done after every successful SNMP set operation. When set to 'enable', config changes are written to the flash which results in slow performance for these set operations. To get faster processing while doing large number of continuous SNMP set operations, this object can be set to 'disable'; And,once the SNMP set operations are done, 'hpSwitchSaveConfig' MIB object can be used to save the running-config to the flash. This object will not be saved across a re-boot, and will always be set to 'enable' at boot. It is advisable to set this MIB object to 'disable' only when there are a lot of continuous SNMP set operations e.g. a script executing a large number of SNMP set operations.

hpSwitchSecureModeLevel.name: hpSwitchSecureModeLevel
hpSwitchSecureModeLevel.description: Indicates current Secure-Mode Level of switch standard : switch operates with standard security capabilities. enhanced : switch operates with enhanced security capabilities for configurations to satisfy FIPS 140-2 requirements.The default level is standard.

hpSwitchStartupConfigSource.name: hpSwitchStartupConfigSource
hpSwitchStartupConfigSource.description: Indicate the method of change to startup config was initiated.

hpSwitchStartupConfigSourceIPAddrType.name: hpSwitchStartupConfigSourceIPAddrType
hpSwitchStartupConfigSourceIPAddrType.description: Indicates the source address type of network agent which made a change. Not valid (set to zero) if change is made via CLI on system console.

hpSwitchStartupConfigSourceIPAddr.name: hpSwitchStartupConfigSourceIPAddr
hpSwitchStartupConfigSourceIPAddr.description: Indicates the source address of network agent which made a change. Not valid (set to zero) if change is made via CLI on system console.

hpSwitchStartupConfigSourceUsername.name: hpSwitchStartupConfigSourceUsername
hpSwitchStartupConfigSourceUsername.description: Indicates the username of CLI user making the change to startup config. Zero-string if username is not set or change is made via SNMP

hpSwitchStartupConfigThrottled.name: hpSwitchStartupConfigThrottled
hpSwitchStartupConfigThrottled.description: Indicates if notification throttle was activated and one or more notifications were dropped.

hpSwitchStartupConfigChange.name: hpSwitchStartupConfigChange
hpSwitchStartupConfigChange.description: The hpSwitchStartupConfigChange notification signifies that switch's startup config was modified by user/manager. Notifications might be buffered on the system to be sent after throttle delay. In some cases, notifications will be dropped. At such event the next transmitted notification will set flag hpSwitchStartupConfigThrottled

hpSwitchRunningCfgChgNotifyEnable.name: hpSwitchRunningCfgChgNotifyEnable
hpSwitchRunningCfgChgNotifyEnable.description: Indicates whether the SNMP entity is permitted to generate hpSwitchRunningConfigChange notifications. Default is disabled.

hpSwitchRunningCfgChgTransmitInterval.name: hpSwitchRunningCfgChgTransmitInterval
hpSwitchRunningCfgChgTransmitInterval.description: Specifies the transmission interval in seconds for sending running config change traps. Only one running config change trap is sent in this time interval. Default value is 0, indicating there is no limit on sending running config change traps.

hpSwitchRunningCfgChgLatestDateAndTime.name: hpSwitchRunningCfgChgLatestDateAndTime
hpSwitchRunningCfgChgLatestDateAndTime.description: Indicates the date and time of the most recent running config change.

hpSwitchRunningCfgChgCount.name: hpSwitchRunningCfgChgCount
hpSwitchRunningCfgChgCount.description: The total number of running config changes since last reboot.

hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEntriesBumped.name: hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEntriesBumped
hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEntriesBumped.description: The number of times the oldest entry in hpSwitchRunningCfgChgTable was discarded to make room for a new entry.

hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventTable.name: hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventTable
hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventTable.description: A table of latest 32 running configuration change events.

hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventEntry.name: hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventEntry
hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventEntry.description: Information about running configuration change event on this switch.

hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventId.name: hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventId
hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventId.description: Identifies a specific running config change. Monotonically increasing values will be assigned by the system to each event as it occurs. If the system is reset, these event ID values will be reset as well.

hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventMethod.name: hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventMethod
hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventMethod.description: Indicates the source through which change to running config was initiated.

hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventSourceIPAddrTy.name: hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventSourceIPAddrType
hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventSourceIPAddrTy.description: Indicates the source address type of network agent which made a change. This object value is set to an address type of unknown when not applicable.

hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventSourceIPAddr.name: hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventSourceIPAddr
hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventSourceIPAddr.description: Indicates the source address of network agent which made a running config change. The value is an address of length 0 (unknown(0)) if not available or not applicable.

hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventUsername.name: hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventUsername
hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventUsername.description: Indicates the username of the user making the change the change to running config. Empty string (length 0) if username is not available or not applicable.

hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventDateAndTime.name: hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventDateAndTime
hpSwitchRunningCfgChgEventDateAndTime.description: Indicates the date and time of the running config change.

hpSwitchRunningConfigChange.name: hpSwitchRunningConfigChange
hpSwitchRunningConfigChange.description: Notification of a running configuration change event as recorded in hpSwitchRunningCfgChgTable.

hpSwitchCdpRunMode.name: hpSwitchCdpRunMode
hpSwitchCdpRunMode.description: Indicates the mode of CDP processing. This variable has no effect when CDP is disabled (cdpGlobalRun = FALSE).

hpSwitchIgnoreUntagMacPortList.name: hpSwitchIgnoreUntagMacPortList
hpSwitchIgnoreUntagMacPortList.description: Prevent learning MAC addresses on the specified ports when the VLAN is untagged and the destination MAC address is one of the following: 01000C-CCCCCC (CDP) 0180c2-00000e (LLDP) 0180c2-000003 (EAPOL)

hpSwitchControlPlaneProtectionAdminStatu.name: hpSwitchControlPlaneProtectionAdminStatus
hpSwitchControlPlaneProtectionAdminStatu.description: The operational status of the Control Plane Protection feature. When Control Plane Protection feature is enabled on a device, if the number of IP error packets exceed the threshold value they are dropped at the data plane. This eliminates the processing of error packets by control plane, thereby reducing the load on the CPU.

hpSwitchRESTInterfaceStatus.name: hpSwitchRESTInterfaceStatus
hpSwitchRESTInterfaceStatus.description: The object that can be used to enable or disable the REST interface. The default value is enable.

hpSwitchRESTSessionIdleTimeout.name: hpSwitchRESTSessionIdleTimeout
hpSwitchRESTSessionIdleTimeout.description: The time period after which the REST session timeout occurs. A user can configure this parameter. The default value is 600 seconds.

hpSwitchCdpPreStdVoiceTable.name: hpSwitchCdpPreStdVoiceTable
hpSwitchCdpPreStdVoiceTable.description: Information about cdp pre-standard-voice admin status for each port in this device.

hpSwitchCdpPreStdVoiceEntry.name: hpSwitchCdpPreStdVoiceEntry
hpSwitchCdpPreStdVoiceEntry.description: Information about cdp pre-standard-voice admin status for a switch port.

hpSwitchCdpPreStdVoiceIfIndex.name: hpSwitchCdpPreStdVoiceIfIndex
hpSwitchCdpPreStdVoiceIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the local interface.

hpSwitchCdpPreStdVoiceStatus.name: hpSwitchCdpPreStdVoiceStatus
hpSwitchCdpPreStdVoiceStatus.description: Indicates the admin status for cdp pre-standard-voice mode for this cdpInterfaceIfIndex entry Default is txAndRx and this value is valid only if hpSwitchCdpRunMode is 'preStdVoice(3)' .

hpSwitchFPModuleConfigTable.name: hpSwitchFPModuleConfigTable
hpSwitchFPModuleConfigTable.description: A table that contains the configuration details for flexible modules.

hpSwitchFPModuleConfigEntry.name: hpSwitchFPModuleConfigEntry
hpSwitchFPModuleConfigEntry.description: An entry in the table that contains the configuration details of a flexible module.

hpSwitchFPModuleConfigType.name: hpSwitchFPModuleConfigType
hpSwitchFPModuleConfigType.description: The J-Number of the flexible module. When set to a value other than none, the value can only be changed to none. Setting this object to none (0) erases the flexible module configuration .

hpSwitchFPModuleConfigName.name: hpSwitchFPModuleConfigName
hpSwitchFPModuleConfigName.description: The flexible module name in the switch. Some devices do not support configuration of the flexible module name and will return an error if this object is set.

hpSwitchBasicConfigCompliance.description: The compliance statement for config entities which implements basic configuration of the switch.

hpSwitchBasicConfigCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for config entities which implements basic configuration of the switch.
